------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party components and why this project is GPL-3.0-or-later
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Nyx is built on GPUI, the UI framework from the Zed project
(https://github.com/zed-industries/zed). The `gpui` / `gpui_platform` framework
crates are themselves licensed under Apache-2.0. However, GPUI's dependency tree
pulls in utility crates from the Zed monorepo that are licensed
GPL-3.0-or-later, reached transitively as:

    gpui -> sum_tree -> ztracing -> zlog
                        ztracing -> ztracing_macro

  - zlog            GPL-3.0-or-later
  - ztracing        GPL-3.0-or-later
  - ztracing_macro  GPL-3.0-or-later

Because these GPL-3.0-or-later components are linked into the Nyx binary, the
distributed binary as a whole is licensed under the GPL-3.0-or-later. Nyx's own
source is GPL-3.0-or-later to match.

The full dependency-license inventory is enforced in CI by `cargo-deny`
(see `deny.toml`). Apache-2.0 is one-way compatible into GPLv3, so the Apache-2.0
components (GPUI and the bulk of the crate graph) are included under the terms of
the GPL-3.0-or-later combined work.
